This sample shows how to create an Avalonia app that can run on Windows, Linux, macOS, Android and iOS.

This sample uses Ab4d.SharpEngine.AvaloniaUI library that provides SharpEngineSceneView control.
  
To see how to build the app for **macOS** and **iOS**, see 
[Quick building instructions for macOS and iOS](https://github.com/ab4d/Ab4d.SharpEngine.Samples/blob/main/README.md#building-for-macos-and-ios) or
[Step by step instructions to run the samples on macOS and iOS](https://github.com/ab4d/Ab4d.SharpEngine.Samples/blob/main/README.md#step-by-step-instructions-to-run-ab4dsharpengine-on-macos-and-ios)

Note that folder and file names in this solution have been shortened to prevent problems with max path size on Windows (260 chars).